comments: Williams III (BOS) establishes himself in VanVleet's (TOR) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Williams III (BOS) establishes himself in VanVleet's (TOR) path and does not deliver illegal contact.

Achiuwa's (TOR) arm is slightly extended as he rolls towards the basket and marginal contact occurs with VanVleet's (TOR) head. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Achiuwa (TOR) initiates contact with Brogdon's (BOS) body, which affects his driving shot attempt.
VanVleet (TOR) briefly engages with White (BOS) off-ball and marginal contact occurs as VanVleet releases away to retrieve the pass.
Williams (BOS) deflects the ball out of bounds. TOR should have retained possession of the ball.
Brogdon (BOS) leans forward and uses his off-arm to clear space from Achiuwa (TOR), which affects Achiuwa's ability to defend the drive.
VanVleet (TOR) brings his arms slightly forward and marginal contact occurs with Brown (BOS) during the screen.
White (BOS) and Siakam (TOR) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Siakam (TOR) is in the lane for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Achiuwa (TOR) makes contact with the ball after it begins it's downward flight toward the basket, and has a chance to score.
Muscala (BOS) moves alongside Barnes' (TOR) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Williams III (BOS) turns to roll and incidental contact occurs with VanVleet (TOR) as he goes under the pick.
Achiuwa (TOR) legally defends Brogdon (BOS) and marginal contact occurs as he attempts to pass
White (BOS) extends his arms and initiates contact with Achiuwa's (TOR) body during his dunk attempt.
Siakam (TOR) initiates contact with Brogdon's (BOS) arm on the perimeter, affecting his SQBR.
Brogdon (BOS) legally contests VanVleet's (TOR) jump shot attempt.
